Description: Buff pottery ostracon: on one side (convex) only, ten lines of an incomplete list of priced commodities.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: S. Birch, 'Inscriptions in the Hieratic and Demotic Character, from the Collections of the British Museum' (London 1868), pl. XXIV; J. J. Černy and A.H. Gardiner, ‘Hieratic Ostraca’ (Oxford 1957), p. 23 and pl. LXXXV, 2; J.J. Janssen, 'Commodity Prices from the Ramessid Period' (Leiden, 1975), p. 78; K. Kitchen, 'Ramesside Inscriptions' Vl (Oxford 1983), 163.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (136359) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/136359)
